*vdr-1.1.26-r1 (11 Apr 2003)
  11 Apr 2003; M.Hierling <mad@cc.fh-lippe.de> vdr-1.1.26-r1.ebuild
  changed to vdr-vanilla, added PROVIDE Flag, removed elchi, 

  03 Apr 2003; H.Ryll <henning.ryll@web.de> rc.vdr-1.1.26
*vdr-1.1.26 (19 Mar 2003)
  04 Apr 2003; M.Hierling <mad@cc.fh-lippe.de> vdr-1.1.26.ebuild
  added the libs to the installation (needed by some dvb tools)

  03 Apr 2003; H.Ryll <henning.ryll@web.de> rc.vdr-1.1.26
  handling of _EXTRAOPTS fixed
  
  03 Apr 2003; M.Hierling <mad@cc.fh-lippe.de> vdr-1.1.26.ebuild
  added support for the irexec programm to restart vdr with a 
  userdefined key (edit /etc/vdr/irexec.conf and start irexec)

  19 Mar 2003; M.Hierling <mad@cc.fh-lippe.de> vdr-1.1.26.ebuild
  new vdr version, some fixes to install all config files
  new download location (cadsoft instead of linuxtv)

*vdr-1.1.25-r3 (15 Mar 2003)
  15 Mar 2003; M.Hierling <mad@cc.fh-lippe.de> vdr-1.1.25-r3.ebuild
  added use variable for VFAT (USE="vdr_vfat")
  added use variable for Elchi AIO (USE="vdr_elchi")
  The supplied Elchi 1.1.25 patch is nothing new, it is the
  1.1.20 patch but packed new to be applied without the nasty
  ofset warnings

*vdr-1.1.25-r2 (14 Mar 2003)
  14 Mar 2003; M.Hierling <mad@cc.fh-lippe.de> vdr-1.1.25-r2.ebuild
  added a watchdog daemon script and the appropriate init script

*vdr-1.1.25-r1 (24 Feb 2003)
